				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">On the topic of palette swaps. I've read a few documents and came to know that palette swapping between an HUD (as long as it doesn't contain sprites) and the game portion is possible and not too hard. If minor graphical glitches are tolerated, then it won't consume too much time either.<br />However it becomes very problematic if one wants to do a palette swap within the game region e.g. splitting the game region into two blocks and use different palettes for them.<br /><br />The specific case is, I have a few blank scanlines to spend, but the protagonist's sprites still need to display correctly on these scanlines.<br />So:<br />&gt; Is it possible at all?<br />&gt; If not, any alternative solutions to make it involve least noticable graphical glitches?</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

