				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">I don't know a way to avoid it other than making a level so that objects of interest never overlap the seam, which could work on some specific platforming stage layouts. <br /><br />Just switching the common bg colour should be even faster than overwriting a full palette entry, if that helps.<br /><br />One last option i can think of is playing with timed emphasis bits to get rows of different colour, but again, sprite presentation will be affected.</div>

					
						<div class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://www.frankengraphics.com">http://www.frankengraphics.com</a><!-- m --> - personal NES blog</div>
